==English==

===Etymology===
Modified Latin, from Greek ''[[ἀμνησία]]'' 'forgetfulness'.

===Pronunciation===
{{ipacregion|Canada}} {{ipac|ˌæmˈniʒə|en-ca-synth-amnesia.ogg|CA synth}}

===Noun===
'''amnesia'''

# {{pathology}} Loss of memory; forgetfulness. Also, a defect of speech, from cerebral disease, in which the patient substitutes wrong words or names in the place of those he wishes to employ.

